--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages telnet.

Telnet is a popular protocol for logging into remote systems over the Internet.
The package provides a command line Telnet client.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: telnet
       telnet_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: telnet
       telnet_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  telnet_state
    Specify predetermined 'telnet_state' variable (string).

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DEPENDENCIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PACKAGES
  telnet: >= 0.17
    CentOS, RedHat

  telnet-bsd: >= 1.2
    Gentoo

